INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '78e69b63-4789-4a8d-a06b-ac7e0335814b',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$tRPC WebSockets — Connection Lifecycle, Heartbeat, Reconnection, and Rooms$escape$,
  $escape$tRPC's WebSocket support lives in `@trpc/server/adapters/ws` on the server and `createWSClient` on the client. The server uses `applyWSSHandler({ wss, router, createContext })`, which wires the raw `ws.Server` into tRPC's subscription machinery. Every `subscription` procedure returns an `observable<T, Error>`, and tRPC manages the open/message/close lifecycle internally — you don't touch raw WebSocket events.

For reconnection, `createWSClient` accepts a `retryDelay` callback: `(attemptIndex) => Math.min(1000 * 2 ** attemptIndex, 30_000)`. tRPC replays pending subscriptions automatically after reconnect, so clients re-enter any active observable without extra logic.

Heartbeats are controlled via `WebSocketServer`'s `clientTracking` + a ping interval you set on the raw `wss`. tRPC doesn't abstract this — set `wss.options.perMessageDeflate` and fire `ws.ping()` on an interval, terminating clients that don't pong.

Rooms are modeled as filtered subscriptions. Pass a `roomId` as subscription input, and use an in-process `EventEmitter` keyed by room. Emit on the correct key; each subscriber's observable only receives matching events. No separate room protocol needed.$escape$,
  $escape$// server.ts
const ee = new EventEmitter();

export const appRouter = router({
  room: t.procedure
    .input(z.object({ roomId: z.string() }))
    .subscription(({ input }) =>
      observable<{ message: string }>(({ next }) => {
        const handler = (msg: { message: string }) => next(msg);
        ee.on(`room:${input.roomId}`, handler);
        return () => ee.off(`room:${input.roomId}`, handler);
      })
    ),
});

// client.ts
const wsClient = createWSClient({
  url: 'ws://localhost:3001',
  retryDelay: (i) => Math.min(1000 * 2 ** i, 30_000),
});
const trpc = createTRPCClient<AppRouter>({ links: [wsLink({ client: wsClient })] });$escape$,
