INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'b9a6bf24-c30b-4f89-9ecc-c42bddf2053d',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$tRPC Authentication — JWT, API Keys, and mTLS via Context and Middleware$escape$,
  $escape$tRPC authentication lives entirely in two places: `createContext` and procedure middleware. Never do auth inside a procedure directly.

In `createContext`, extract the Authorization header and verify your JWT using a library like `jose`. Attach the decoded payload to ctx — or null if invalid. This gives every procedure access to `ctx.user` without repeated parsing.

For API key auth (e.g. server-to-server), follow the same pattern: parse `x-api-key`, look it up in your DB inside `createContext`, attach the result. Don't re-query per procedure.

Guard routes with a reusable `authedProcedure` built via `t.procedure.use(({ ctx, next }) => { ... })`. Throw `TRPCError({ code: 'UNAUTHORIZED' })` if `ctx.user` is null. Compose further: `adminProcedure = authedProcedure.use(requireRole('admin'))`.

For mTLS, termination happens at the proxy layer (nginx/APIM). Pass a verified-client header downstream; read it in `createContext` just like a JWT. tRPC itself is transport-agnostic — the chain stays identical regardless of how the token arrives.$escape$,
  $escape$// server/trpc.ts
const createContext = async ({ req }: CreateNextContextOptions) => {
  const token = req.headers.authorization?.split(' ')[1];
  let user: JWTPayload | null = null;
  if (token) {
    try { user = (await jwtVerify(token, secret)).payload; }
    catch { /* invalid token — user stays null */ }
  }
  return { user };
};

const authedProcedure = t.procedure.use(({ ctx, next }) => {
  if (!ctx.user) throw new TRPCError({ code: 'UNAUTHORIZED' });
  return next({ ctx: { user: ctx.user } }); // narrows type to non-null
});

export const userRouter = router({
  profile: authedProcedure.query(({ ctx }) => getProfile(ctx.user.sub)),
});$escape$,
  $escape$typescript$escape$,
